summary: Completed comprehensive testing of TimeKeeper time tracking platform. Backend APIs working well (89.5% success rate), frontend UI and core functionality working excellently (95%+ success rate). Main issue: admin role assignment not working for existing users.

admin_issues.issue: Admin role not assigned to admin@timekeeper.com users
admin_issues.details: Users registered with admin@timekeeper.com get 'user' role instead of 'admin' role

integration_issues.issue: Admin users cannot access /admin route due to role mismatch

design_issues.issue: React warning about duplicate keys in color selection
React warning about setState during render in BrowserRouter

passed_tests: Timer start/stop functionality with real-time counting
Navigation between all pages (Dashboard, Entries, Reports, Projects)
All CRUD operations for projects and time entries

success_percentage.frontend: 95% (core functionality working, minor admin access issue)

action_item_for_main_agent: Fix admin role assignment: Ensure users with email 'admin@timekeeper.com' get 'admin' role during registration. Current implementation assigns 'user' role to all users including admin@timekeeper.com.
